cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper focuses on machine translation, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and is a subfield of computational linguistics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with multimodal machine translation, which involves incorporating visual features into the translation process. This requires computer vision techniques and knowledge of image processing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes adapting the Transformer neural machine translation architecture to a multimodal setting. This involves training a machine learning model to perform the translation task. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with developing an AI system for multimodal machine translation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimodal machine translation, which involves processing multiple modalities such as text and images. This falls under the domain of multimedia processing.
